## 5. Muscle Groups & Body Map

The interactive body map is a core differentiator. Here's how it works:

### Supported Muscle Groups (14 groups)

| Region | Front View | Back View |
|--------|-----------|-----------|
| **Neck/Traps** | ✓ | ✓ |
| **Shoulders (Delts)** | ✓ | ✓ |
| **Chest (Pecs)** | ✓ | — |
| **Biceps** | ✓ | — |
| **Forearms** | ✓ | ✓ |
| **Abs (Core)** | ✓ | — |
| **Obliques** | ✓ | — |
| **Quads** | ✓ | — |
| **Calves** | ✓ | ✓ |
| **Upper Back (Lats)** | — | ✓ |
| **Lower Back** | — | ✓ |
| **Triceps** | — | ✓ |
| **Glutes** | — | ✓ |
| **Hamstrings** | — | ✓ |

### Body Map Interaction Flow

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A[User sees SVG body - front & back] --> B[Hover highlights muscle]
    B --> C[Click selects muscle group]
    C --> D[Side panel opens]
    D --> D1[Date range picker: 7d / 30d / 90d / All]
    D --> D2[Total exercises targeting this muscle]
    D --> D3[Total volume: sets × reps × weight]
    D --> D4[Frequency: sessions per week]
    D --> D5[Last trained date]
    D --> D6[Top exercises bar chart]
```

### Heatmap Coloring

Muscles are color-coded based on training frequency over the selected period:

| Frequency | Color | Meaning |
|-----------|-------|---------|
| 0 sessions | Gray `#c0c0c0` | Not trained |
| 1-2 sessions | Light blue `#90caf9` | Under-trained |
| 3-4 sessions | Green `#66bb6a` | Moderate |
| 5-7 sessions | Orange `#ffb74d` | Well-trained |
| 8+ sessions | Red `#ef5350` | Heavily trained |

